<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="20997">Notes</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="20997">
Reported from Greece by 
<bibRefCitation author="Arvanitidis, Christos" journalOrPublisher="PhD thesis. Aristotle University of Thessaloniki, Thessaloniki" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" title="Συστηματική και βιονομική μελέτη των μακροβενθικών πολυxαίτων (AnnelidaPolychaeta) του Βορείου Αιγαίου" year="1994">Arvanitidis (1994)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Chatzigeorgiou, G" journalOrPublisher="Hellenic Centre for Marine Research" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" title="Polychaetes from two subtidal rocky shores of the North coast of Crete, collected for the NaGISA project 2007 - 2008." year="2016">Chatzigeorgiou et al. (2016)</bibRefCitation>
. The relationships within the species of the 
<taxonomicName class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Filograna" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Filograna" order="Sabellida" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">Filograna</taxonomicName>
/ 
<taxonomicName class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Salmacina" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Salmacina" order="Sabellida" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">Salmacina</taxonomicName>
complex and the characters used to distinguish species and genera are still a matter of debate (
<bibRefCitation author="Nogueira, Joao Miguel de Matos" journalOrPublisher="Beaufortia" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" pagination="151 - 161" title="On a new species of Salmacina Claparede, 1870 (Polychaeta: Serpulidae) from Sao Paolo state, Brazil" volume="50" year="2000">Nogueira and ten Hove 2000</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Filograna" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Filograna" order="Sabellida" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">Filograna</taxonomicName>
is usually considered operculate and 
<taxonomicName class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Salmacina" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Salmacina" order="Sabellida" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">Salmacina</taxonomicName>
non-operculate, but mixed colonies have been found, questioning the validity of the character. 
<bibRefCitation author="Fauvel, P." journalOrPublisher="Paul Lechevalier, Paris" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" title="Faune de France. Polychetes sedentaires" year="1927">Fauvel (1927)</bibRefCitation>
considers the three taxa 
<taxonomicName class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Filograna" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Filograna implexa" order="Sabellida" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="implexa">Filograna implexa</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Salmacina" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Salmacina dysteri" order="Sabellida" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="dysteri">Salmacina dysteri</taxonomicName>
(Huxle, 1855) and 
<taxonomicName class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Salmacina" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Salmacina incrustans" order="Sabellida" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="incrustans">Salmacina incrustans</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken originalValue="Claparède">Claparede</normalizedToken>
, 1870 to be separate species, a view which is also tentatively followed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Nogueira, Joao Miguel de Matos" journalOrPublisher="Beaufortia" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" pagination="151 - 161" title="On a new species of Salmacina Claparede, 1870 (Polychaeta: Serpulidae) from Sao Paolo state, Brazil" volume="50" year="2000">Nogueira and ten Hove (2000)</bibRefCitation>
until more information becomes available. They recommend using locally applied names for each of the species. We follow this view here and list all three species as separate, pending further taxonomic investigation. Greek specimens were identified using the key of 
<bibRefCitation author="Bianchi, Carlo Nike" journalOrPublisher="Guide per il riconoscimento delle specie animali delle acque lagunari e costiere italiane" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" pagination="1 - 187" title="Policheti Serpuloidei" volume="5" year="1981">Bianchi (1981)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
